# Quizly Installation

To install Quizly, run the generator:

```bash
rails generate quizly:install
```

This will:

1.  Copy all necessary migrations to your application.
2.  Copy locale files (`en.yml`, `ar.yml`) to `config/locales`.
3.  Create an initializer file (`config/initializers/quizly.rb`) for configuration.

After running the generator, you should run your migrations:

```bash
rails db:migrate
```

## Configuration

Edit `config/initializers/quizly.rb` to customize settings:

```ruby
Quizly.configure do |config|
  # config.default_locale = :en
  # config.shuffle_questions = true
  # config.shuffle_choices = true
end
```